content.detailedDescription: I was reading in bed and i had just finished so i turned the light out. i had been in the dark for no more than a minute when i saw a green light illuminating my room and the room outside my door. i sat up and looked out the window and witnessed a green orb decending from above the housd to the second floor window adjacent to me. i could hear what sounded like large gears rotating even though the window and wall. the orb then entered through the window affecting nothing physically. the sound of rotating gears was quite loud at this point and i had been watching it move from behind what served as a temporary door. the orb moved half way into the room before i got up to approach it and had been no more than 10 feet from where i was standing. i slowly and quietly began to approach the door because i had wanted to see it up close and personal, touch it if possible. yet when i got to the door and tried to go out the orb moved at incredible speed back through the window as if it were not even there and accended rapidly into the sky and out of sight. this event was not ball lightning yet i do not particularly expect anyone to believe me. this orb however expressed awareness and inteligence and when it knew i had been aware of it. it flew away. this is not my first experience and i am sure it will not be my last.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Green orb that sounded like rotating gears

content.detailedDescription:
In back yard of client around 8:30 pm on 2/13/16 in gulf breeze, fl. clear view of night sky, few lights around - 100% viz. looking up as i always do when the sky is so clear and stars bright. saw what i thought was a meteor about 40deg above horizon to the south. i thought it was a meteor because of the speed. i t was very dim compared to the brightness of the stars. i expected it to burn out, but i had to physically turn around as i followed it across the sky, where it went out of sight behind trees to the north about 30deg above horizon. the object appeared grayish to copper with fuzzy edges, appearing translucent at the edges - not reflecting ground light, but emitting it's own light. as i pivoted my body and head to watch the object speed across the sky, i verbally said, "oh my god, what the heck was that!" my wife, who was in the house heard me, was alarmed and came out of the house. the object had zipped by across the entire arc of the sky without changing in brightness, velocity or direction. i was astonished by the speed and the fact that it did not burn out or change in brightness, nor did it appear to decelerate. the object appeared solid with "fuzzy" or translucent edges and was chevron in shape and grayish-brown in color. my impression was that it was at a very great distance, in the upper atmosphere, making its apparent speed all the more astonishing.

i have tried to make sense of this, but i know of nothing conventional or natural that would explain it. i hesitated to post this report, but i ultimately felt a responsibility to report this in the hope it might contribute in some small way to your efforts.
content.summary: Clear night sky. object, meteor-like speed though not bright, 40deg above horizon from south, 3-4 seconds across sky to north.

when arrived home, we were able to see the same yellow dot as the first step. it was doing the same kind of pattern as the step 1. (file 3.Png)

content.detailedDescription:
My daughter looked up and observed a huge ball of light in the night sky, over the hawaii marine base where she lives w/her husband. (whom is military police.) she watched for a bit, as it was so much bigger and brighter than everything else in the sky. thats when it started pulsing and moving around.  it would get dimm, then extremely bright over and over as it maneuvered around.  she realized it was much closer. maybe a mile away in the sky. she then became amazed so she called a friend (neighbor)and the cell phones went to static. when her friend walked over, she began observing the object as well. after apx 15 mind. or so....It went off and was gone. immediately the entire island lost all power.Then....They witnessed aircraft that seemed to be circling the surrounding areas. no one has explained what happened yet. so she's a bit un-nerved but excited. so she calls me and tells me her story because she knows i would believe her. (as we saw a similar event happen in nc (near monroe)back in 2008 that she witnessed with me. she then confides that she saw something similar about 3- months ago. then again about 3- nights ago. now this. so she is now a bit more concerned of what it could be and what is going on. she is surrounded by military and definitely knows what those aircraft look and sound like. this was not an aircraft she is familiar with. considering it also had no sounds!  she wanted me to report it as she is worried about her military connection. however she is willing to talk to someone.
her phone number is (386)-299-5518 and please be discreet as she is a little hesitant for above said reasons. though... we both feel these occurrences need reported and investigated. we are wondering if anyone else reported it. it seems many, many, observed it but are too reluctant to report it. also, because of their military connections. 
we are fans of james fox and his work at mufon so we are hoping it is taken seriously.  thank you for your time, and listening. 😃 
 (daughter's name is chelsey)

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking with my wife near prospect park in brooklyn when i noticed a shiny white orb in the sky. i soon observed that there were three, flying in what appeared to be a triangular formation. each looked identical to the others: shiny white, reflective, with fuzzy edges. as these orbs made their way across the sky, several more followed. there were seven or eight in total. as best i could tell, the orbs moved very swiftly across the sky at a distance greater than 1 mile from where we stood. 

my wife and i were soon joined by two other couples who stopped to watch with us. one woman mentioned that they looked like balloons. but, again, these orbs moved very swiftly -- faster than the airplanes you see in the distant sky. they looked similar to the ufo orbs i have seen in videos on the internet and on the news. they had no contrail and were noiseless. they did not make any erratic turns or movements, nor did they appear to vanish or "blink" away. they simply continued on, moving steadily northeast, until the naked eye could no longer observe them. their direction of travel was uniform, although it did appear that some of the orbs moved toward each other while others moved apart.

during the sighting i felt excited and curious, a rush of elation. i wanted to see more, i wanted them to descend -- but it was not to be. this is my second sighting, the first being in 2007 also in brooklyn. on this occasion the orbs were much closer, glowed orange and blue, and followed a nonlinear flight trajectory.
content.summary: A group of 7 to 8 white orbs traveling in a formation or a cluster quite fast across the sky.

content.detailedDescription: Smoking a cig on my deck as usual. i'm watching planes go by when i notice this red light not blinking . it was moving to fast for normal aircraft i see. once i watched it i saw a vapor trail. that was strange because everything that flies over has at least 2 trails if its comercial. i timed it from n. to s. at 45 seconds. that is moving, because a jet at 5000ft. takes 150 seconds. and an airline at 36,000ft. takes close to 3 minuets.Also all aircraft either military or commercial that i see always have blinking lamps. always! most have more than one
content.summary: Oval craft moving fast w/red light(not blinking) leaving a single vapor trail

content.detailedDescription:
We were vacationing in north eastern arizona. stayed at a small motel in the middle of nowhere near winslow if i remember correctly. in the morning at apx 9:00 am we were packing to leave. we were taking advantage of a window near our van, and passing baggage outside. my wife took the picture. pictured are myself, and my young son and daughter. the van is in the background. the window is obviously open, with no screen. there was nothing in the area. no traffic, wind, birds, or clouds noticed. very quite morning with nothing unusual. 

this photo has been one in an album that i use for a desk top screen saver for several years. a couple days ago i happened to be looking in the right place when it flashed on the screen and i noticed this spot in the background sky almost directly in the middle of the window, about 20 degrees above the eastern horizon. curious, i went back to the photo and started zooming in to see what it might be. to me, its a ufo. 

you decide.

i'm a firm believer that we are not alone. it is ludicrous to even consider it. this photo just reinforces my belief.
content.summary: Photo captured, object not noticed in photo until 15 years later.

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my condo's parking lot walking to my unit. i looked north and saw a bright light at about the height of commercial airlines in final approach to the airport. it was a bright like landing lights but singular; not dual typical of commercial aircraft. i questioned whether or not i was observing an aircraft, or a star. there was a thin cloud cluster moving north and when i first saw the light i question whether the object was moving or was it a an illusion caused by the cloud cluster moving north. it became apparent that the light was moving south. during the entire period of observation i never observed aircraft strobe lights.
the star-like object was travelling south. when it got at about 10 o'clock, the brightness diminished. it was then i realized the object gained altitude. at about 2 o'clock, the object disappeared at a very high altitude. the moon was bight and i lost visual on the object about a hands width from the moon.
overall the object was first observed heading south at approach height. it made a gradual turn to the southeast while gaining altitude and then disappeared.
my condo is under one of the flight path to one of the airports. i have seen many aircraft in final approach. this was not like anything i had ever observed before. i have never seen any aircraft do what i observed last night. this object did not fly over. it disappeared. when it disappeared the sky was clear and except for the cloud cluster mentioned at the beginning of the observation, the sky was clear.
content.summary: Star-like

content.detailedDescription:
1. heading west on cr 232 near cr 337 near osceloa community center. i was driving home from a day of work and school. 

2.Something to my right just so happened to catch my eye. 

3. wtf is that??????? is that flames around it? awfully round for an aircraft.

4. round, solid black, heading west, was to my right and in front, it was maintaining a steady speed in excess of 75 (which is what i was doing), appeared to have some kind a orangish/blue ring around it, similar to what would be in a blacksmiths forge. its course seemed to be heading west, true and straight, no vertical or lateral motion. 

5. feelings were mixed, still is. was tired from work and aggravated because of school at the time, wasn't sure if my mind was playing tricks on me. even now, feelings are still mixed, since i don't normally believe in flying saucers, but by definition what i saw was a ufo. 

6. lost sight when road dipped, and object went behind the line of trees on my right. never did regain visual contact since the area i was coming up on is very well wooded.
content.summary: Round, black, flame like ring encircling object
